"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-07-29-paris-2024-olympics-bello-wraps-up-team-nigerias-poor-display-in-table-tennis\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Debutant Fatima Bello has been eliminated from the 2024 Olympic Games after a comprehensive defeat to Jia Nan Yuan of France on Monday.  Bello lost the table tennis women's singles Round of 64 contest 4-0 (1-11, 3-11, 3-11, 5-11).  She struggled to cope with her opponent's Swiftness and precision.  Her exit ended Team Nigeria's hope of winning a medal in the table tennis event.  Aruna Quadri, Olajide Omotayo, and Effiong Edem have all exited the competition.  Since the inception of table tennis at the 1988 Olympics, this is the first time that no Nigerian table tennis player registered at least one win.  Transfer: Man Utd offered Inter Milan star in swap deal for Wan-Bissaka  Transfer: Napoli to offer Osimhen in exchange deal for Chelsea striker  Phone-tapping equipment: ICPC now political weapon - El-Rufai's son, Bello  Akpabio, Bello: Senator Natasha alleges some VIP's use power to witch-hunt others  2027: Bello resigns from APC, says he's 'out of bondage'  El-Rufai's son, Bello abandons father, SDP, backs Tinubu for second term  Akpabio, Bello used fake constituents to initiate my recall process - Natasha  Bello vs EFCC: Court fixes May 8 for ruling on admissibility of Abuja court judgment  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"